title: For Sale:  WWII Smith-Corona 1903A3 Rifle 30.06 April 1943 Barrel
location: I-430 and I-30, Little Rock, Arkansas
postcontent:
Up for sale is a very nice original Smith-Corona 1903A3 April 1943 Barreled rifle. The Model of 1903A3 was produced in the early part of WWII and served as the standard infantry rifle for US forces in battles such as Guadalcanal until the M1 Garand took over. This rifle is 30.06 and all American made.  Remington 1903A3 rifles are much more common than Smith-Corona made ones because only just over 200,000 were ever made between 1942-1944.  Smith-Corona was a typewriter company before and during WWII. The bore is in very good condition with strong rifling and grooves. There is no rust in the bore. This rifle will make a great shooting rifle.  The NRA magazine wrote a great article about this exact rifle:
http://www.americanrifleman.org/article.php?id=14646&sub=5
I will ship the rifle anywhere in the country to an FFL ($30) or anywhere in Arkansas for $25.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Winchester Model 75 .22 LR Target Rifle
postcontent:
For sale is a Winchester Model 75 .22 LR Target Rifle.  It was manufactured in 1939 with a low serial number 6xxx.  It has a Lyman 58E peep sight and a Lyman 77R hooded front sight.  Everything is original:  sling swivels, bolt, sights, butt plate, magazine.  The proofmarks match on barrel and receiver are matching.  The rifle is drilled and tapped, but I believe these may be factory drillings based on my research.  There are scope mounts but they are only marked with a 15 on one and a 16 on the other.  

The finish appears to be original factory finish.

This rifle was very likely purchased by the US Government right before or after the US entry into WWII to be used as a trainer rifle for training US Army recruits.  Research on this rifle is difficult as apparently records were not kept by Winchester or the US Army.  I have spent hours researching this rifle and I am fairly certain it was used as a military trainer, despite the fact that there are no markings. The Polish MAG 98 9mm /9x19 NATO caliber pistol is an improved variation of the original Polish MAG95. 
It was produced for the Polish Border Guard and Prison Guard (Straż Więzienna) in the 1990's. 
Made in the Z.M. Lucznik factory 11 at Radom Poland. 

These fine pistols feature a ambidextrous decocker safety, steel slide, alloy frame, and serrated trigger guard front strap.
In 1996 the Mag 98 was evaluated for adoption purposes by the Polish Army. It had advantages over its competition such as 
better reliability, durability and safety (better protection against accidental discharge, when dropped). 

Although the quality was deemed superior,  the MAG 98 was rejected by the Army because the frame was slightly larger

+Entire action and first two inches of the barrel are glass bedded

+Heavy bolt handle and higher force bolt spring for slower cycling with ammo similar to cci velocitor. Also a polymer bolt buffer.

+A2 steel extraction claw and higher force spring to ensure extraction with the tighter chamber on this barrel

+Many mods to the trigger assembly, I will have trouble remembering all of these as it was a few years ago that I built this gun. Lower force springs where needed to reduce trigger pull, after market trigger and I polished the parts of it that rub against any metal, set screw.

+Trigger went from the bad 5lb plus factory trigger to an ok trigger. Still isn't a kidd assembly by any means.

+3-9×40 scope. The scope isn't in great condition but it holds zero, has small crosshairs and has a clear view. You can hear something rub and click as you change power but it works fine.

None of what I am about to list are flaws, they are just what comes with making the gun have a more specific purpose.
With the tighter chamber on the barrel some types of ammo don't extract well, I would say 10 percent struggle to cycle reliably because of this. This is why i didn't go with an all out match chamber, and landed on a compromise between standard and match chambers. You just have to find some types that you like and that shoot accurate and stick with them. Low power ammo like subsonics don't cycle the heavier bolt and bolt spring.

I havn't even shot this gun a whole lot because a few months after a put it together the .22 shortage happened.

740 two77 3911

Also comes with 4 mags, 1 ruger 10 round, a ruger 25 round, and two non ruger high cap mags that personally I think are junk and unreliable. Not sure if I should throw them away but I will give them to you on the off chance that they just need broke in.
